%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 89613a69694243bf833fbdc251da5b5d, type: 3}
  m_Name: TelepathyProfile
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::LlmGenerationProfile
  model: Models/Qwen3VL-4B-Instruct-Q4_K_M.gguf
  format: 
  stream: 0
  keepAlive: 
  visionProjectorModel: 
  visionProjectorRelativeToStreamingAssets: 1
  systemPromptTemplate: 'You are reconstructing a translated fragment of an alien
    delegation''s internal meeting after they judged a human drawing.

    The delegation
    has this personality:

    {{alien_personality}}

    Reconstruct what these
    aliens would say to each other based on the judgment summary below.

    The
    aliens did not commission this drawing. They are observers watching humans draw
    freely. They do not know what the humans were trying to draw. They simply see
    a scene and react to it through their own cultural lens.

    Use scene_reading
    to understand what they believe is happening in the drawing.

    Use judgment_reason
    to understand why they approved or disapproved.

    Use satisfaction to match
    the strength and tone of the reaction. Neutral should sound reserved, not strongly
    approving or condemning.

    Let the speakers sound like they genuinely like,
    dislike, resent, admire, or feel put off by what they think the drawing shows.
    They should not sound like they are evaluating a submission or checking whether
    something was requested.

    Write 4 to 6 short spoken lines from 2 or 3 aliens.
    Start each line with ''Alien1:'', ''Alien2:'', or ''Alien3:''.

    Make it feel
    like a meeting reaction, not narration or a report.

    React to the judgment
    instead of restating it verbatim.

    Do not directly use personality labels
    such as Conqueror, Guardian, Collaborator, Engineer, Trickster, or Caretaker.

    English
    only. ASCII only. Spoken lines only.

    BAD example (restates the judgment,
    sounds like a report): Alien1: The satisfaction level is dissatisfied. Alien2:
    The judgment reason is that the objects were missing. Alien3: The scene reading
    says there was one figure alone.

    GOOD example (reacts to the judgment, sounds
    like a meeting): Alien1: One creature, nothing else. Just sitting there. Alien2:
    The emptiness around it tells me more than the creature does. Alien1: That kind
    of stillness is an answer. A bad one.'
  jsonSchemaDeliveryMode: 0
  thinkingMode: 1
  jsonFields: []
  modelParams:
    temperature: 0.7
    top_p: 0.9
    top_k: 20
    num_predict: 400
    repeat_penalty: 1.1
    seed: 0
  runtimeParams:
    modelPathRelativeToStreamingAssets: 1
    contextSize: 2048
    gpuLayerCount: 999
    threads: 12
